        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-11-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-11-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="257" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by General <persName type="from">Chen
                            Cheng</persName> to General <persName type="to">Marshall</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-11-09">November 9,
                            1946</date>.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The President of the Chinese Government issued an order to all the troops in
                    China on 8 November to stop fighting and to remain in their present positions.
                    This order will become effective at 12 o’clock noon 11th November. Please notify
                    the Communist Representative, and ask him to attend the meeting of the Committee
                    of Three to discuss cease fire measures. Prompt transmission of this information
                    to the Communist representative and an early reply would be appreciated.</p>
            </div>
